1
00:00:01,293 --> 00:00:04,505
[ HARMONICA PLAYING ]

2
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:22,189
[ ENGINES SLOWING ]

3
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:32,867
Archer: Archer to
Commander Tucker.

4
00:00:32,908 --> 00:00:34,326
GO AHEAD.

5
00:00:34,368 --> 00:00:37,621
I know you're off-duty,
but we've got visitors.

6
00:00:37,663 --> 00:00:38,914
I CAN SEE THAT.

7
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:40,958
Are you up
for a little repair work?

8
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,918
SIR?

9
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,920
Meet me at docking port 2.

10
00:00:44,962 --> 00:00:46,964
ON MY WAY.

11
00:00:52,803 --> 00:00:57,140
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

12
00:00:57,182 --> 00:01:00,477
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

13
00:01:00,519 --> 00:01:04,231
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

14
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:07,776
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

15
00:01:07,818 --> 00:01:12,322
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

16
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:15,826
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

17
00:01:15,868 --> 00:01:19,997
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

18
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:23,124
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

19
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,920
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

20
00:01:25,961 --> 00:01:28,087
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

21
00:01:28,129 --> 00:01:31,132
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

22
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:35,930
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

23
00:01:35,971 --> 00:01:38,432
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

24
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:43,228
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

25
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:46,023
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

26
00:01:46,065 --> 00:01:51,820
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

27
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,697
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

28
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:56,033
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

29
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:59,912
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

30
00:01:59,954 --> 00:02:04,416
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

31
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,349
ANYTHING SERIOUS?

32
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:23,184
ARCHER: THEY SAID
THEY WERE HAVING TROUBLE

33
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:25,312
WITH ONE OF THEIR
LIFE-SUPPORT SYSTEMS.

34
00:02:25,353 --> 00:02:26,396
TRIP: WHO'S "THEY"?

35
00:02:26,438 --> 00:02:28,774
T'POL: RETELLIAN CARGO PILOTS.

36
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:33,737
THE SEAL IS SECURE.

37
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:40,077
WELCOME ABOARD.

38
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:45,082
ALIEN: GRACIOUS OF YOU
TO HELP US, CAPTAIN.

39
00:02:45,124 --> 00:02:47,084
WE WERE BEGINNING TO THINK
OUR DISTRESS CALL

40
00:02:47,126 --> 00:02:48,669
WOULD NEVER BE ANSWERED.

41
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,337
ARCHER: THIS IS
SUBCOMMANDER T'POL

42
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:52,840
AND MY CHIEF ENGINEER,
COMMANDER TUCKER.

43
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,299
ALIEN: OUR SALVATION.

44
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:57,385
TRIP: THE CAPTAIN SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT LIFE SUPPORT.

45
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:58,637
WE WERE HIRED

46
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,015
TO RETURN A YOUNG WOMAN
TO HER HOMEWORLD.

47
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:02,641
A FEW DAYS AGO,

48
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:04,893
HER STASIS POD
BEGAN TO MALFUNCTION.

49
00:03:04,935 --> 00:03:06,061
ARCHER: STASIS?

50
00:03:06,103 --> 00:03:07,604
IS SHE INJURED?

51
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:09,023
NO, NO.

52
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:10,482
SHE'S A PASSENGER.

53
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:14,153
BUT OUR SHIP IS DESIGNED
TO HAUL CARGO, NOT PEOPLE,

54
00:03:14,193 --> 00:03:16,655
AND IT'S A VERY LONG JOURNEY.

55
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:18,532
PUTTING HER
IN SUSPENDED ANIMATION

56
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:20,034
WAS OUR ONLY CHOICE.

57
00:03:20,075 --> 00:03:22,077
ALIEN: WE HAVE ANOTHER FIVE
MONTHS AHEAD OF US.

58
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:24,038
IF SHE WAKES UP,

59
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,789
THERE WON'T BE ENOUGH
FOOD, AIR TO BREATHE.

60
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:27,666
IF WE'RE FORCED TO
ABORT THE MISSION,

61
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:29,835
WE WON'T GET...PAID.

62
00:03:29,877 --> 00:03:31,962
COMMANDER TUCKER
IS RESOURCEFUL.

63
00:03:32,004 --> 00:03:35,423
I'M SURE HE'LL BE ABLE
TO ASSIST YOU.

64
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,592
TRIP: MIND IF I HAVE A LOOK?

65
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:39,260
PLEASE.

66
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:46,309
YOU'VE BEEN VERY ACCOMMODATING.

67
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:47,728
IF IT'S NOT TOO MUCH TROUBLE,

68
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:50,022
I'D LIKE TO MAKE
ANOTHER REQUEST.

69
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:51,815
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME

70
00:03:51,857 --> 00:03:54,193
SINCE WE'VE ENJOYED
THE LUXURY...

71
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,070
OF A BATH.

72
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:58,113
OH. I UNDERSTAND.

73
00:03:58,155 --> 00:04:00,074
T'POL WILL SHOW YOU
TO GUEST QUARTERS.

74
00:04:00,115 --> 00:04:01,491
WHEN YOU'RE DONE,

75
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:04,119
I'LL HAVE MY CHEF
PREPARE YOU A MEAL.

76
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:24,098
ALIEN: THIS REGULATES POWER FLOW
TO THE BIO-POD.

77
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:26,058
LOOKS VERY CREATIVE.

78
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:29,352
THESE RELAYS ARE FROM
AN OLD ARDANAN SHUTTLE.

79
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:32,022
THEY WEREN'T DESIGNED TO
CARRY THIS MUCH CURRENT.

80
00:04:32,064 --> 00:04:36,443
I'VE GOT SOME E.P.S. CONDUITS
THAT MIGHT DO THE TRICK.

81
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:47,495
TRIP: THIS'D BE A LOT EASIER
IF I COULD READ YOUR LANGUAGE.

82
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:48,997
IF YOU DON'T MIND,
I'D LIKE TO ASK

83
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:51,250
OUR COMMUNICATIONS OFFICER
TO GIVE ME A HAND.

84
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,710
ALIEN: BY ALL MEANS.

85
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:07,099
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

86
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:10,894
NO.

87
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:12,479
NO, NO PROBLEM.

88
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,815
I'M GOING TO NEED SOME TOOLS
FROM<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

89
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:16,650
WITH A LITTLE LUCK,

90
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:20,361
"SLEEPING BEAUTY" HERE WILL
NEVER KNOW THERE WAS A PROBLEM.

91
00:05:29,204 --> 00:05:30,789
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

92
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,249
COME IN.

93
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:38,255
I HOPE I DIDN'T DEPLETE
YOUR WATER SUPPLY.

94
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:40,299
I'M SURE WE'LL MANAGE.

95
00:05:40,339 --> 00:05:41,925
PLEASE.

96
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:47,181
T'POL TELLS ME YOUR VESSEL
CAN'T DO MUCH BETTER

97
00:05:47,222 --> 00:05:49,224
THAN WARP 2.

98
00:05:49,266 --> 00:05:50,349
WARP 2.2.

99
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:53,645
I'VE BEEN MAKING
SOME CALCULATIONS.

100
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:56,690
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN,
AT WARP 4.5,

101
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:59,193
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> CAN HAVE YOU
AT YOUR DESTINATION

102
00:05:59,234 --> 00:06:01,153
IN LESS THAN FOUR DAYS.

103
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:02,904
THAT'S A GENEROUS OFFER,

104
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:05,657
BUT I'VE ALREADY
INCONVENIENCED YOU FAR TOO MUCH.

105
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,075
IT'S NO INCONVENIENCE.

106
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:09,619
WE'RE OUT HERE
TO MEET NEW PEOPLE.

107
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:11,830
YOU'RE HEADING
TOWARD AN INHABITED WORLD

108
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,248
WE'VE NEVER SEEN.

109
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:16,168
FIRST CONTACTS TEND TO GO
MORE SMOOTHLY

110
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:19,129
WHEN A FAMILIAR FACE
IS MAKING THE INTRODUCTIONS.

111
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:21,840
I'M SURE YOU'LL DO FINE
ON YOUR OWN.

112
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,885
YOU COULD DOCK
IN OUR LAUNCH BAY.

113
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:28,180
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT THAT STASIS POD.

114
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:31,892
WE HAVE PLENTY OF ROOM
FOR YOU AND YOUR PASSENGER.

115
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,727
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE, CAPTAIN.

116
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:36,855
THIS HAS ALL BEEN
CAREFULLY PREARRANGED.

117
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,566
HER FAMILY IS NOT EXPECTING HER
FOR ANOTHER FIVE MONTHS.

118
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:42,986
THEY'RE NOT EVEN ON HER
HOME WORLD AT THE MOMENT.

119
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:46,740
BUT I WILL ACCEPT YOUR OFFER
OF A MEAL...

120
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,700
IF IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

121
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,843
COMMANDER?

122
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,143
HELLO?

123
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:17,604
IS THAT
THE TRANSLATION?

124
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:19,522
GIVE OR TAKE AN ADVERB.

125
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:21,233
THANKS.

126
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:24,694
AT LEAST YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORK ALONE.

127
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:26,654
HELL OF A WAY
TO TRAVEL, ISN'T IT?

128
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,115
WHO IS SHE? ANY IDEA?

129
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,574
I ASKED PLINN,

130
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:31,285
BUT HE DOESN'T SEEM TO
KNOW TOO MUCH ABOUT HER.

131
00:07:31,326 --> 00:07:32,953
SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
STUDYING MEDICINE

132
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:34,371
AT A RESEARCH COLONY.

133
00:07:34,413 --> 00:07:36,331
HOSHI: A DOCTOR?
TRIP: I SUPPOSE SO.

134
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:38,458
SHE MUST HAVE
A REAL PASSION FOR IT

135
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:42,003
IF SHE'S WILLING TO
GO THROUGH ALL THIS.

136
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:43,922
SHAME WE'LL NEVER
GET TO MEET HER.

137
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:47,759
IT'S NOT POLITE TO STARE,
COMMANDER.

138
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,470
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED
TO MEAN?

139
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:52,055
LET ME KNOW
IF YOU HAVE ANY PROBLEMS

140
00:07:52,097 --> 00:07:53,640
WITH THAT TRANSLATION.

141
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:56,310
I WASN'T STARING.

142
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:02,690
[ THUMPING ]

143
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,651
HOSHI?

144
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:07,487
[ THUMPING CONTINUES ]

145
00:08:09,239 --> 00:08:10,782
[ MUFFLED SCREAMING ]

146
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:12,326
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

147
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,535
[ SHOUTING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE ]

148
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:17,080
[ BEEPING ]

149
00:08:17,122 --> 00:08:18,248
ARCHER: PROBLEM?

150
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:19,333
ALIEN: THE STASIS POD.

151
00:08:19,374 --> 00:08:20,959
T'POL: WHAT ABOUT IT?

152
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:22,502
ALIEN: IT'S MALFUNCTIONING.

153
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:23,962
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
CAPTAIN.

154
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:26,381
T'POL: I'LL SHOW YOU TO
THE DOCKING PORT.

155
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:28,091
ALIEN: I KNOW THE WAY.

156
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,093
[ MUFFLED SCREAMING ]

157
00:08:33,430 --> 00:08:34,889
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

158
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:36,141
HELP ME OPEN THIS THING!

159
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:37,434
WE CAN'T BRING HER
OUT OF STASIS.

160
00:08:37,476 --> 00:08:38,643
TRIP: SHE'S SUFFOCATING!

161
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:41,480
THE RELEASE IS JAMMED!
DON'T BOTHER!

162
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:46,526
WOMAN: [ GASPING, SCREAMING ]
TRIP: I'M SORRY ABOUT THIS,

163
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,944
BUT THE 02 RECYCLER
WENT OFF-LINE.

164
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:49,363
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

165
00:08:49,404 --> 00:08:51,114
YOU'RE GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

166
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:56,911
[ BEEPING ]

167
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:58,121
YES?

168
00:08:58,163 --> 00:08:59,456
ALIEN: THERE'S A MINOR PROBLEM.

169
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:01,041
I'M GOING TO NEED
YOUR ASSISTANCE.

170
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:02,376
WHAT KIND OF PROBLEM?

171
00:09:02,417 --> 00:09:04,002
ALIEN: THE MALFUNCTION
IS MORE COMPLICATED

172
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,712
THAN I EXPECTED.

173
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:08,382
I'LL BE THERE IN A MOMENT.

174
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:09,966
I DON'T MEAN TO BE RUDE.

175
00:09:10,008 --> 00:09:11,676
ARCHER: NOT AT ALL.

176
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:17,807
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

177
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:20,185
ARCHER TO COMMANDER TUCKER.

178
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:24,272
TRIP, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

179
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,863
ARCHER TO LIEUTENANT REED.

180
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,283
MR. PLINN?

181
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:36,535
THAT'S RIGHT.

182
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,036
LIEUTENANT REED.
THE CAPTAIN ASKED ME

183
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:39,413
TO ESCORT YOU BACK
TO YOUR SHIP.

184
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:40,705
PLINN: THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

185
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:42,749
I'M AFRAID I'M UNDER ORDERS.

186
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,125
HAVE I DONE SOMETHING WRONG?

187
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:46,336
IT'S JUST A PRECAUTION.

188
00:09:46,378 --> 00:09:48,838
I NEVER REALIZED
LEAVING THE CAPTAIN'S TABLE

189
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,549
WOULD CAUSE SO MUCH CONCERN.

190
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:23,498
HE'S TRYING TO BREAK LOOSE.

191
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:25,875
SECURE THE DOCKING CLAMPS.

192
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,350
REPORT.

193
00:10:42,392 --> 00:10:45,145
HE HASN'T GOTTEN FAR
AT WARP 2, SIR.

194
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,521
HAIL HIM.

195
00:10:46,563 --> 00:10:49,524
HOSHI: NO RESPONSE.

196
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:51,901
PHASE CANNONS.

197
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:53,612
TARGET HIS ENGINES.

198
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:58,199
DIRECT HIT TO THE PORT NACELLE.

199
00:10:58,241 --> 00:11:00,118
HE'S DROPPING OUT OF WARP.

200
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:07,792
BRING US INTO GRAPPLING RANGE.

201
00:11:07,834 --> 00:11:09,628
HAIL HIM AGAIN.

202
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,631
TRAVIS: CAPTAIN.

203
00:11:17,552 --> 00:11:19,220
T'POL?

204
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:22,140
DILITHIUM HYDROXYLS...
IONIZED PYROSULFATES.

205
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:24,601
TRAVIS: HE'S MOVING OFF.

206
00:11:24,643 --> 00:11:27,228
STAY WITH HIM.

207
00:11:34,152 --> 00:11:36,237
I THOUGHT YOU TOOK OUT
ONE OF HIS NACELLES?

208
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:37,489
SO DID I.

209
00:11:37,531 --> 00:11:39,199
TRAVIS: OUR WARP DRIVE
WON'T ENGAGE.

210
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,535
REED: THAT CLOUD HE RELEASED,
IT GOT INTO THE PLASMA VENTS.

211
00:11:41,576 --> 00:11:43,495
THEY'LL HAVE TO BE PURGED.

212
00:11:43,537 --> 00:11:47,541
TRAVIS: HE'S MOVING
OUT OF SENSOR RANGE.

213
00:11:47,582 --> 00:11:49,292
I'VE LOST HIM.

214
00:11:53,672 --> 00:11:56,299
[ GROANS ]

215
00:11:57,884 --> 00:11:59,927
[ THUNK ]
[ GROANS ]

216
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,720
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

217
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:02,930
OH, WHAT THE HELL

218
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:04,307
DID YOU DO THAT FOR?

219
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:05,766
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

220
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:07,352
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

221
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:10,230
I'M NOT WORKING WITH THEM.

222
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,401
CALM DOWN.

223
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:16,528
I'M NOT GOING TO HURT YOU.

224
00:12:16,570 --> 00:12:20,323
I'M -- I'M FROM A STARSHIP...
CALLED<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

225
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:21,908
UH...<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

226
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:24,369
NOW...

227
00:12:24,411 --> 00:12:25,995
PUT THAT THING DOWN

228
00:12:26,037 --> 00:12:28,707
AND I'LL UNTIE YOU.

229
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:29,916
YOUR HANDS...

230
00:12:29,957 --> 00:12:31,959
I'LL FREE YOUR HANDS.

231
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:34,962
LET ME HELP YOU.

232
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:38,049
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

233
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:42,887
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

234
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:44,514
ALIEN: IS IT REPAIRED?

235
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:45,724
WHAT?

236
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:46,933
ALIEN: THE STASIS POD.

237
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,351
WHERE'S CAPTAIN ARCHER?

238
00:12:48,393 --> 00:12:51,271
YOUR SHIP
IS A LONG WAY FROM HERE.

239
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,481
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

240
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:56,943
REPAIR THE POD SO WE CAN
PUT HER BACK IN STASIS.

241
00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:59,696
IT'S GOING TO TAKE A FEW HOURS.

242
00:12:59,738 --> 00:13:02,031
WORK QUICKLY.

243
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:08,787
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

244
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:16,963
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

245
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:19,633
UH...YOU'RE WELCOME?

246
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:26,180
HAVE YOU SEEN A-A LITTLE DEVICE?

247
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:28,099
UM, IT'S ABOUT THIS BIG.

248
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:31,269
IT HAS A-A KEYPAD ON IT.

249
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:34,188
UM...IT'S
MY UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR.

250
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:37,108
IT'LL HELP US UNDERSTAND
EACH OTHER.

251
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,155
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

252
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,991
THAT'S IT!

253
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:48,620
IT'S -- IT'S JUST
SO WE CAN TALK.

254
00:13:56,336 --> 00:13:58,171
I NEED YOU TO SAY SOMETHING.

255
00:13:58,212 --> 00:13:59,297
YOU GOT TO KEEP TALKING.

256
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:03,426
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

257
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:06,262
[ TRANSLATOR BEEPING ]

258
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:08,014
A LITTLE MORE.

259
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:10,933
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

260
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:17,607
CAN YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

261
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:20,777
WHERE'S HOSHI
WHEN YOU NEED HER?

262
00:14:20,819 --> 00:14:22,028
WHO IS HOSHI?!

263
00:14:22,069 --> 00:14:24,322
THAT'S BETTER.

264
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:27,283
WOULD YOU MIND TELLING ME
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

265
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:30,495
HOW LONG HAVE
I BEEN IN STASIS?

266
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:33,832
WELL, YOU'D HAVE TO ASK THEM.

267
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:36,751
COMMANDER TUCKER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

268
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:39,587
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i> DO YOU HEAR ME?

269
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:42,089
YOU ARE AN OFFICER?

270
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:45,343
CHIEF ENGINEER.

271
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:48,346
FEELS LIKE WE'VE GONE TO WARP.

272
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:49,514
EXPLAIN YOURSELF.

273
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:51,766
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT MY ABDUCTORS?

274
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,976
WE THOUGHT
THEY WERE CARGO PILOTS.

275
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:56,521
THEY CLAIMED
YOU WERE THEIR PASSENGER.

276
00:14:56,563 --> 00:14:57,856
I AM THEIR PRISONER.

277
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,191
I WAS RETURNING
FROM A DIPLOMATIC MISSION

278
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:02,527
WHEN THEY ATTACKED
MY TRANSPORT...

279
00:15:02,569 --> 00:15:06,280
MURDERED MY GUARDS.

280
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:09,534
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO I AM, DO YOU?

281
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:10,744
SHOULD I?

282
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:14,997
MY FAMILY IS KNOWN
ON HUNDREDS OF WORLDS.

283
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:18,710
WELL, I'M AFRAID
EARTH ISN'T ONE OF THEM.

284
00:15:18,752 --> 00:15:20,378
SO, I TAKE IT
YOU'RE NOT A DOCTOR.

285
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:23,130
I AM FIRST MONARCH
OF THE SOVEREIGN DYNASTY

286
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:25,633
OF KRIOS PRIME.

287
00:15:25,675 --> 00:15:27,301
OH.

288
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:30,096
CHARLES TUCKER III.

289
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:32,139
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

290
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:34,058
SO, WHAT DO THESE GUYS WANT?

291
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,976
RANSOM.

292
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,855
NO DOUBT THEY'LL DEMAND
A HIGH PRICE FOR MY SAFE RETURN.

293
00:15:38,897 --> 00:15:41,190
LISTEN, MY CAPTAIN
WILL BE LOOKING FOR ME.

294
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:43,234
ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS GET OFF THIS SHIP

295
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:44,778
AND LET HIM KNOW
WHERE WE ARE.

296
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:47,363
AND HOW DO YOU PROPOSE
WE DO THAT?

297
00:15:47,405 --> 00:15:48,782
I SAW A SHUTTLE BAY EARLIER.

298
00:15:48,823 --> 00:15:50,658
THERE WERE
A COUPLE OF ESCAPE PODS.

299
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,786
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

300
00:15:52,827 --> 00:15:54,412
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

301
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:57,957
WE'LL REMAIN HERE UNTIL THEY
CONTACT THE SOVEREIGN GUARD.

302
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,794
ONCE THE RANSOM HAS BEEN PAID,
WE'LL BE RELEASED.

303
00:16:00,835 --> 00:16:02,462
WELL, IF IT'S ALL
THE SAME TO YOU,

304
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:04,130
I'D RATHER TAKE
MY CHANCES IN OPEN SPACE.

305
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,423
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

306
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:07,508
IF YOU LEAVE,
IT WOULD PROVOKE THEM.

307
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,218
IF I REMEMBER RIGHT,

308
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:12,138
THIS ACCESS TUBE LEADS TO
A JUNCTION NEAR THE SHUTTLE BAY.

309
00:16:12,179 --> 00:16:14,098
YOU ARE NOT TO LEAVE
THIS CHAMBER.

310
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:19,437
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
I'M NOT ONE OF YOUR SUBJECTS.

311
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:30,364
HE'S YOUR PARTNER.

312
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,826
YOU MUST HAVE SOME IDEA
WHERE HE'S GOING.

313
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,578
OBVIOUSLY,
I'M HIS VICTIM, AS WELL.

314
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:38,038
WHY ELSE WOULD
HE LEAVE ME HERE?

315
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,541
WHERE WERE YOU TAKING
YOUR PASSENGER?

316
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:42,543
GOFF HAD THE COORDINATES.

317
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:45,254
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT SYSTEM
YOU WERE HEADING FOR?

318
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:46,840
IT WASN'T MY RESPONSIBILITY.

319
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:49,843
HE WAS PILOTING
THE SHIP, NOT ME.

320
00:16:49,884 --> 00:16:52,219
I SPENT MOST OF MY TIME
LOOKING AFTER THE CARGO.

321
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,888
BELIEVE ME, CAPTAIN,

322
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:58,768
I'M AS EAGER TO FIND
MY<i> PARTNER</i> AS YOU ARE.

323
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,190
IF THAT'S TRUE...

324
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:06,400
THEN WE COULD
WORK TOGETHER

325
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:08,194
TO TRACK HIM DOWN.

326
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:10,530
I DON'T SEE HOW.

327
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,866
WE'VE GOT PRETTY GOOD
LONG-RANGE SENSORS,

328
00:17:12,907 --> 00:17:14,617
BUT YOUR SHIP
COULD BE ANYWHERE

329
00:17:14,659 --> 00:17:16,703
WITHIN A HALF DOZEN
LIGHT-YEARS.

330
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:19,914
IT'D BE A LOT EASIER
IF WE KNEW YOUR WARP FREQUENCY.

331
00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:22,834
WELL, I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T HELP YOU WITH THAT.

332
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:26,253
I KNOW VERY LITTLE
ABOUT WARP ENGINES.

333
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:30,842
TAKE HIM BACK
TO DOCKING PORT 2.

334
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:34,220
PUT HIM IN THE AIRLOCK
AND POST A SECURITY DETAIL.

335
00:17:34,261 --> 00:17:36,055
I'M TELLING YOU THE TRUTH!

336
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,016
WE'LL KEEP
THE OUTER HATCH UNLOCKED.

337
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:41,185
IF YOU DECIDE TO LEAVE,
YOU KNOW THE WAY OUT.

338
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:48,985
COULD YOU HAND ME
THAT CIRCUIT PROBE?

339
00:17:49,027 --> 00:17:51,946
THE ONE WITH THE GREEN HANDLE?

340
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:59,495
YOU MUST BE ONE
HELL OF A DIPLOMAT.

341
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:01,247
IS YOUR ENTIRE SPECIES

342
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:02,665
SO ILL-MANNERED?

343
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:05,543
NO...JUST ME.

344
00:18:05,585 --> 00:18:07,879
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WERE
THINKING RATIONALLY,

345
00:18:07,921 --> 00:18:09,881
YOU'D BE REPAIRING
THAT STASIS POD.

346
00:18:09,923 --> 00:18:12,550
HE<i> DID</i> THREATEN TO KILL YOU.

347
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:14,594
THAT'S PRECISELY WHY
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

348
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,596
I REALLY DOUBT
THEY'RE GOING TO KEEP ME AROUND

349
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:19,933
ONCE I FIX THEIR PROBLEM.

350
00:18:19,974 --> 00:18:22,226
YOU KNOW, I REALIZE
SOMEONE IN YOUR POSITION

351
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:24,812
ISN'T USED TO TAKING ADVICE
FROM A GUY LIKE ME...

352
00:18:24,854 --> 00:18:27,314
BUT I STRONGLY SUGGEST
YOU COME ALONG.

353
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:28,775
HE'D NEVER HARM ME.

354
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:30,484
I'M TOO VALUABLE TO THEM.

355
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:33,153
I'VE BEEN INVOLVED
IN A FEW HOSTAGE SITUATIONS.

356
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:36,032
THEY RARELY TURN OUT
THE WAY YOU EXPECT.

357
00:18:37,992 --> 00:18:39,911
YOU'RE CORRECT, MR. TUCKER.

358
00:18:39,953 --> 00:18:43,039
I DON'T TAKE ADVICE
FROM PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

359
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:45,332
[ POP ]

360
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,126
YOU KNOW...

361
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:50,421
THAT STASIS POD
WON'T FIX ITSELF.

362
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,551
CHANCES ARE YOU'RE GOING TO
SPEND THE NEXT FIVE MONTHS

363
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:57,678
TIED UP IN THIS GRIMY
LITTLE CARGO HOLD.

364
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:59,597
NOT EXACTLY MY IDEA
OF A ROYAL VOYAGE.

365
00:18:59,639 --> 00:19:02,141
I'LL BE FINE.

366
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:04,018
WHEN I GET BACK TO<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>

367
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:06,145
I'LL MAKE SURE WE GET
A MESSAGE TO YOUR HOME WORLD.

368
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:07,354
PRIOS...?

369
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:09,356
KRIOS PRIME.

370
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:12,944
TAKE CARE.

371
00:19:12,986 --> 00:19:14,695
WOMAN: ONCE YOU'VE LAUNCHED
AN ESCAPE POD,

372
00:19:14,737 --> 00:19:17,281
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
THEY WON'T DESTROY IT?

373
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:19,617
I'M GOING TO REROUTE
THEIR INTERNAL SENSORS.

374
00:19:19,659 --> 00:19:21,995
I'LL BE A MILLION KILOMETERS
AWAY BEFORE THEY KNOW

375
00:19:22,036 --> 00:19:23,997
I'M GONE.

376
00:19:24,038 --> 00:19:27,625
I'M MUCH BETTER COMPANY.

377
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:29,877
HOW MUCH FURTHER?

378
00:19:29,919 --> 00:19:31,879
JUST A FEW MORE METERS.

379
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:34,340
ARE YOU SURE
THIS IS THE RIGHT DIRECTION?

380
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:36,134
KEEP YOUR VOICE DOWN.

381
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:39,386
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO CALL YOU,
ANYWAY?

382
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:42,389
FIRST MONARCH?

383
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:44,600
YOUR HIGHNESS?

384
00:19:44,642 --> 00:19:46,352
KAITAAMA.

385
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:49,313
WHAT IS THAT,
SOME KIND OF A TITLE?

386
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:51,024
IT'S MY NAME.

387
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:53,400
OH.

388
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:55,402
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

389
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:59,782
THESE LEAD TO INTERNAL SENSORS.

390
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,503
WE DON'T HAVE ALL DAY.

391
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:30,688
THIS IS MEANT FOR ONE PERSON.

392
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:32,439
WE'LL HAVE TO MAKE DO.

393
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:35,484
UNLESS YOU KNOW HOW TO FLY
ONE OF THESE THINGS.

394
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:02,803
[ GROANS ]

395
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:28,246
WHAT WAS THAT?

396
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:31,082
WE'RE CROSSING
THE SUBSPACE THRESHOLD.

397
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,754
[ SIGHS ]
THAT WASN'T SO BAD.

398
00:21:36,796 --> 00:21:40,424
KAITAAMA: WHAT DO YOU
PROPOSE WE DO NEXT?

399
00:21:40,466 --> 00:21:43,510
TO BE HONEST, I HADN'T
REALLY THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

400
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:45,846
I ASSUMED YOU HAD A PLAN.

401
00:21:45,888 --> 00:21:47,723
I WAS ONLY JOKING.

402
00:21:47,765 --> 00:21:49,516
THEY DO HAVE A SENSE OF HUMOR

403
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,018
WHERE YOU COME FROM?

404
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:53,187
AMONG THE COMMONERS.

405
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:55,355
ONLY JOKING.

406
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:56,690
UNH...

407
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:58,525
IT'S ONLY A MATTER OF TIME

408
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:00,444
BEFORE THEY REALIZE WE'RE GONE.

409
00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:02,947
NO DOUBT THEY'LL COME
ABOUT AND LOOK FOR US.

410
00:22:02,989 --> 00:22:04,198
WE NEED A PLACE TO HIDE.

411
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,616
WHERE?

412
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,411
IF I'M TRANSLATING THIS RIGHT,

413
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:12,206
THERE'S A SYSTEM ABOUT
90 MILLION KILOMETERS FROM HERE.

414
00:22:12,248 --> 00:22:14,541
WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO
REACH IT IN A DAY OR SO.

415
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:15,668
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK

416
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:17,920
ANY OF THOSE PLANETS
ARE HABITABLE?

417
00:22:17,962 --> 00:22:20,506
ONLY ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

418
00:22:20,547 --> 00:22:23,550
PERMISSION TO SET A COURSE,
YOUR SOVEREIGNTY?

419
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:26,512
PROCEED.

420
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:44,280
TRIP: THIS WOULD BE
A WHOLE LOT EASIER

421
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:45,823
IF YOU'D STOP
MOVING AROUND.

422
00:22:45,865 --> 00:22:47,116
YOU'RE TOUCHING ME.

423
00:22:47,158 --> 00:22:48,784
I'M AFRAID
I DON'T HAVE MUCH CHOICE.

424
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,453
IT'S INAPPROPRIATE
TO TOUCH THE FIRST MONARCH.

425
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:55,582
YOU'RE WELCOME TO STEP OUTSIDE
UNTIL I'M DONE.

426
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:57,584
EXCUSE ME.

427
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,628
THERE WE GO.

428
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:00,880
LANDING THRUSTERS...

429
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,757
OH, NO, WAIT,
THEY'RE STABILIZERS.

430
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:06,552
YOU HAVE NO IDEA HOW
TO CONTROL THIS VEHICLE.

431
00:23:06,593 --> 00:23:08,137
I'M WORKING ON IT.

432
00:23:08,179 --> 00:23:10,472
EVEN IF WE DO FIND
A BREATHABLE ATMOSPHERE

433
00:23:10,514 --> 00:23:12,975
AND YOU MANAGE TO LAND
WITHOUT KILLING US,

434
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:14,476
WHAT WILL WE DO ABOUT FOOD?

435
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:15,895
WATER?

436
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:18,189
THERE COULD BE HOSTILE
LIFE-FORMS ON THE SURFACE.

437
00:23:18,231 --> 00:23:19,940
HOW WILL WE PROTECT
OURSELVES?

438
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,359
LOOK, I'VE GOT LESS
THAN 24 HOURS

439
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:23,110
TO FIGURE OUT HOW
TO SCAN A STAR SYSTEM

440
00:23:23,152 --> 00:23:24,528
AND PROGRAM
A DESCENT SEQUENCE

441
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,197
IN A LANGUAGE
I DON'T UNDERSTAND,

442
00:23:26,239 --> 00:23:27,573
AND I'M NOT GOING
TO GET IT DONE

443
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:29,491
WITH YOU INTERRUPTING ME
EVERY FIVE SECONDS.

444
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:31,244
SO, I'D APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU'D KEEP QUIET

445
00:23:31,285 --> 00:23:34,621
UNTIL I'M FINISHED.

446
00:23:34,663 --> 00:23:36,290
NOW, LIFT YOUR BUTT.

447
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:37,666
MY WHAT?

448
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:39,126
YOUR BEHIND --

449
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:40,294
YOUR REAR END.

450
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:43,381
I HAVEN'T CHECKED
THAT PANEL YET.

451
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:47,885
QUICKLY.

452
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,095
YOU KNOW, YOU WERE

453
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:51,722
A LOT MORE PLEASANT
IN STASIS.

454
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:59,146
I THINK I FOUND
THE LANDING THRUSTERS.

455
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:04,777
I UNDERSTAND HOW DIFFICULT

456
00:24:04,818 --> 00:24:08,072
THIS MUST BE FOR SOMEONE
OF YOUR UPBRINGING.

457
00:24:08,114 --> 00:24:10,408
BUT WE COULD BE STUCK
OUT HERE FOR A WHILE.

458
00:24:10,448 --> 00:24:12,952
WE SHOULD FIND A WAY
TO GET ALONG.

459
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:17,664
I'M WILLING TO GIVE
IT A TRY IF YOU ARE.

460
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:19,625
MY HAND.

461
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:22,711
YOU'RE SITTING ON MY HAND.

462
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:28,968
I'LL TRY.

463
00:24:44,858 --> 00:24:49,155
REED: THE PRISONER, SIR...
AS ORDERED.

464
00:24:55,411 --> 00:24:56,870
ARCHER: THANK YOU.

465
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:59,332
REED: WILL THERE BE
ANYTHING ELSE, CAPTAIN?

466
00:24:59,373 --> 00:25:01,292
ARCHER: NOT RIGHT NOW,
LIEUTENANT.

467
00:25:01,334 --> 00:25:02,709
DISMISSED.

468
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:09,049
HAVE A SEAT.

469
00:25:10,343 --> 00:25:12,719
WHY HAVE I BEEN BROUGHT HERE?

470
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:15,097
SIT DOWN.

471
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:22,146
I ALREADY TOLD YOU
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

472
00:25:22,188 --> 00:25:24,731
WE'RE NOT HERE TO TALK
ABOUT YOUR PARTNER.

473
00:25:24,773 --> 00:25:26,442
WE'RE HERE TO TALK ABOUT YOU.

474
00:25:26,484 --> 00:25:28,568
WHAT ABOUT ME?

475
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:32,781
YOU'RE FACING SOME
VERY SERIOUS CHARGES, MR. PLINN.

476
00:25:32,823 --> 00:25:34,700
WHERE WE COME FROM,

477
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:36,743
CRIMINALS ARE HELD
ACCOUNTABLE

478
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:38,287
FOR THEIR ACTIONS.

479
00:25:38,329 --> 00:25:40,622
IF THEY'RE FOUND GUILTY,
THEY'RE PUNISHED.

480
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:45,294
THIS IS WHERE YOUR TRIBUNAL
IS GOING TO TAKE PLACE.

481
00:25:45,336 --> 00:25:46,753
TRIBUNAL?

482
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:49,465
I AM NOT SUBJECT TO YOUR LAWS.

483
00:25:49,507 --> 00:25:51,467
THAT'S NOT FOR ME TO DECIDE.

484
00:25:56,305 --> 00:26:01,018
STARFLEET ASKED
THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND

485
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:04,562
TO ASSIGN A JUDICIAL
ADMINISTRATOR TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

486
00:26:04,604 --> 00:26:07,191
SOMEONE WHO WOULDN'T BE SWAYED
BY HUMAN EMOTION --

487
00:26:07,233 --> 00:26:09,693
SOMEONE OBJECTIVE, LOGICAL.

488
00:26:09,735 --> 00:26:11,737
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,
SUBCOMMANDER T'POL

489
00:26:11,778 --> 00:26:14,198
HAS ALREADY REVIEWED
THE EVIDENCE.

490
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:17,493
THIS TRIBUNAL...

491
00:26:17,535 --> 00:26:19,828
IS NOTHING MORE
THAN A FORMALITY.

492
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:23,874
I THOUGHT
YOU SHOULD BE PREPARED.

493
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:29,088
HER PUNISHMENTS CAN BE...

494
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:30,797
SEVERE.

495
00:26:30,839 --> 00:26:32,841
HOW SEVERE?

496
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:35,469
IF YOU'RE LATE FOR YOUR SHIFT,

497
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:37,430
YOU MIGHT RECEIVE A BEATING.

498
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:40,807
BUT FOR MORE
GRIEVOUS OFFENSES...

499
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:42,476
DERELICTION OF DUTY,

500
00:26:42,518 --> 00:26:46,480
CONDUCT UNBECOMING AN OFFICER...

501
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:48,482
[ SIGHS ]

502
00:26:48,524 --> 00:26:53,153
WE STARTED OUT
WITH 83 CREWMEN ON BOARD.

503
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:57,366
WE'RE DOWN TO 76.

504
00:26:57,408 --> 00:27:00,077
BUT I HAVEN'T DONE
ANYTHING WRONG!

505
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:01,495
ARCHER: ACCESSORY
TO KIDNAPPING,

506
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:03,456
RESISTING ARREST,

507
00:27:03,497 --> 00:27:05,458
OBSTRUCTION OF AN INVESTIGATION,

508
00:27:05,499 --> 00:27:08,043
CAUSING DAMAGE
TO A STARFLEET VESSEL...

509
00:27:08,085 --> 00:27:09,503
WHAT DAMAGE?

510
00:27:09,545 --> 00:27:11,088
WHEN YOUR PARTNER FLED,

511
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:13,048
HE RELEASED A CLOUD
OF DILITHIUM HYDROXYLS

512
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:14,550
THAT CLOGGED OUR PLASMA VENTS.

513
00:27:14,592 --> 00:27:15,842
I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH THAT.

514
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:17,386
AS I SAID...

515
00:27:17,428 --> 00:27:19,513
I'M NOT THE ONE
YOU HAVE TO CONVINCE.

516
00:27:19,555 --> 00:27:21,223
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

517
00:27:27,271 --> 00:27:29,231
SUBCOMMANDER.

518
00:27:29,273 --> 00:27:33,569
T'POL: HAS THE ACCUSED
BEEN INFORMED OF THE CHARGES?

519
00:27:33,611 --> 00:27:35,279
ARCHER: YES, MA'AM.

520
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:40,867
HOW MUCH DO YOU WEIGH?

521
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:43,537
WHAT?

522
00:27:43,579 --> 00:27:45,872
YOUR WEIGHT.

523
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:48,626
72 KILOGRAMS.

524
00:27:50,461 --> 00:27:52,087
HEIGHT?

525
00:27:52,129 --> 00:27:53,589
1.8 METERS.

526
00:27:53,631 --> 00:27:55,508
WHY ARE YOU ASKING
THESE QUESTIONS?

527
00:27:55,549 --> 00:27:58,427
DOES YOUR CULTURE OBSERVE
ANY POSTMORTEM RITUALS?

528
00:27:58,469 --> 00:28:00,804
THIS IS NOT FAIR!

529
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:04,266
I DEMAND TO SPEAK WITH
SOMEONE FROM MY GOVERNMENT!

530
00:28:04,308 --> 00:28:07,478
HE'S GOT A POINT.

531
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,147
WE'VE NEVER TRIED
AN ALIEN BEFORE.

532
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:13,233
MAYBE WE<i> SHOULD</i> CONTACT
THE HIGH COMMAND.

533
00:28:13,275 --> 00:28:16,612
THEY'VE GRANTED ME COMPLETE
AUTONOMY IN THESE MATTERS.

534
00:28:16,654 --> 00:28:18,572
IF I HAD TO CONSULT
MY SUPERIORS

535
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:20,907
EVERY TIME I MADE A RULING,

536
00:28:20,949 --> 00:28:23,076
IT WOULD DEFEAT MY PURPOSE HERE.

537
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:26,079
WE'LL CONVENE AT 1800 HOURS.

538
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:27,998
ARCHER: AS YOU WISH.

539
00:28:33,128 --> 00:28:35,088
YOU CAN'T ALLOW THIS.

540
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:37,883
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

541
00:28:37,924 --> 00:28:39,051
BUT YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN!

542
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:41,220
[ SIGHS ]

543
00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:46,183
SHE OWES ME A FEW FAVORS.

544
00:28:47,643 --> 00:28:51,438
I CAN'T PROMISE ANYTHING,
BUT I...

545
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,149
I'D BE WILLING
TO ASK FOR LENIENCY.

546
00:28:54,191 --> 00:28:58,862
OF COURSE, I'D WANT
SOMETHING IN RETURN.

547
00:28:58,904 --> 00:29:03,825
WE STILL HAVEN'T FOUND
A WAY TO LOCATE YOUR VESSEL.

548
00:29:05,202 --> 00:29:09,373
IF YOU COULD REMEMBER
THAT WARP FREQUENCY...?

549
00:29:19,966 --> 00:29:21,594
ARE THERE ANY PROVISIONS?

550
00:29:21,635 --> 00:29:23,136
I'M HUNGRY.

551
00:29:23,178 --> 00:29:25,305
YOU MIGHT CHECK THAT
STORAGE COMPARTMENT

552
00:29:25,347 --> 00:29:26,640
ABOVE YOUR HEAD.

553
00:29:26,682 --> 00:29:28,601
YOU DO IT.

554
00:29:28,642 --> 00:29:30,352
I'M BUSY.

555
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:35,315
[ RATTLING ]

556
00:29:35,357 --> 00:29:37,276
IF YOU FIND
ANY WATER UP THERE,

557
00:29:37,317 --> 00:29:39,570
I COULD USE SOME.

558
00:29:41,238 --> 00:29:42,989
THANKS.

559
00:29:50,247 --> 00:29:53,083
ALLOW ME.

560
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,715
I'M NOT CONTAGIOUS.

561
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:09,391
IS IT EDIBLE?

562
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:16,774
WELL, DEPENDS
HOW HUNGRY YOU ARE.

563
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:23,781
REMINDS ME OF MY FIRST CAR.

564
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:25,532
CAR?

565
00:30:25,574 --> 00:30:28,118
A FOUR-WHEELED VEHICLE.

566
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:31,288
WASN'T MUCH BIGGER THAN THIS.

567
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:34,040
ALL WE'RE MISSING
IS THE OCEAN BREEZE

568
00:30:34,082 --> 00:30:36,042
COMING OFF THE GULF.

569
00:30:36,084 --> 00:30:38,295
I USED TO DRIVE OUT

570
00:30:38,337 --> 00:30:41,047
TO A PLACE CALLED
CHATKIN POINT...

571
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:42,633
PARK ALONG THE SHORELINE

572
00:30:42,675 --> 00:30:47,137
AND STARE AT THE MOON
WITH MY GIRLFRIEND.

573
00:30:49,348 --> 00:30:51,391
DON'T WORRY.

574
00:30:51,433 --> 00:30:53,435
I WON'T MAKE A PASS AT YOU.

575
00:30:53,477 --> 00:30:56,313
THE SOVEREIGN GUARD WOULD
CUT OFF ONE OF YOUR HANDS.

576
00:30:56,355 --> 00:30:59,608
YOU MUST BE A FUN DATE.

577
00:30:59,650 --> 00:31:03,696
THE FIRST MONARCH DOESN'T
SOCIALIZE WITH THE OPPOSITE SEX.

578
00:31:03,737 --> 00:31:07,032
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN ON A DATE?

579
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:09,034
FOUR YEARS AGO,

580
00:31:09,075 --> 00:31:12,621
BEFORE I WAS SELECTED
TO ASCEND TO FIRST MONARCH,

581
00:31:12,663 --> 00:31:17,125
I WAS COURTED BY YOUNG MEN
FROM MANY NOBLE FAMILIES.

582
00:31:17,167 --> 00:31:20,003
NOW I SPEND MY PERSONAL TIME

583
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:23,382
IN THE COMPANY
OF MY FATHER'S ADVISORS.

584
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:26,844
SOUNDS KIND OF LONELY.

585
00:31:28,011 --> 00:31:30,972
YOU HAVEN'T FINISHED YOUR WORK.

586
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:47,823
IT'S ALL WATER.

587
00:31:47,865 --> 00:31:50,075
THERE'S A CHAIN OF ISLANDS
NEAR THE EQUATOR.

588
00:31:50,116 --> 00:31:52,327
WILL WE BE ABLE TO BREATHE?

589
00:31:52,369 --> 00:31:55,080
OXYGEN, NITROGEN,
A TRACE OF METHANE.

590
00:31:55,121 --> 00:31:56,415
NOTHING WE CAN'T HANDLE.

591
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:58,751
DO YOU DETECT ANY LIFE-FORMS?

592
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:01,294
IF I COULD FIGURE OUT
HOW TO USE THE BIO-SENSORS.

593
00:32:01,336 --> 00:32:04,172
ARE YOU CERTAIN WE HAVE
THE CORRECT PLANET?

594
00:32:04,214 --> 00:32:07,885
IT'S THE ONLY ONE
WITH AN ATMOSPHERE.

595
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:11,638
YOU MAY BEGIN OUR DESCENT.

596
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:15,183
LET'S HOPE I GET THIS RIGHT.

597
00:32:23,149 --> 00:32:26,445
WE'RE ENTERING THE THERMOSPHERE.

598
00:32:26,486 --> 00:32:27,738
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

599
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:29,197
THE PORT STABILIZER'S DOWN.

600
00:32:29,239 --> 00:32:30,657
CAN YOU REPAIR IT?

601
00:32:30,699 --> 00:32:33,535
NO, BUT THE STARBOARD ONE
SHOULD KEEP US ON COURSE.

602
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:41,543
MR. TUCKER!

603
00:32:41,585 --> 00:32:43,462
SO FAR SO GOOD.

604
00:32:43,503 --> 00:32:46,089
8,000 METERS.

605
00:32:46,131 --> 00:32:47,215
I THINK THEY'RE METERS.

606
00:32:47,257 --> 00:32:49,802
7,000.

607
00:32:49,843 --> 00:32:51,136
I'M PRETTY SURE

608
00:32:51,177 --> 00:32:53,263
THE BRAKING THRUSTERS
ARE FIRING.

609
00:32:53,305 --> 00:32:54,723
5,000 METERS.

610
00:32:54,765 --> 00:32:57,935
YOU MIGHT WANT TO GRAB HOLD
OF SOMETHING.

611
00:33:04,483 --> 00:33:06,234
2,000 METERS.

612
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:09,154
1,000...

613
00:33:11,949 --> 00:33:13,199
HOLD ON.

614
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:14,952
[ CRASH ]

615
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:15,994
[ HISSING ]

616
00:33:16,035 --> 00:33:17,203
YOU ALL RIGHT?

617
00:33:17,245 --> 00:33:18,664
WHAT IS THAT?

618
00:33:18,705 --> 00:33:20,206
DAMNED IF I KNOW.

619
00:33:20,248 --> 00:33:21,875
[ GROANS ]

620
00:33:21,917 --> 00:33:25,921
[ BIRDS CALLING,
INSECTS BUZZING ]

621
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:56,994
KAITAAMA:
THIS HEAT IS UNBEARABLE.

622
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:59,037
TRIP: IT'S NOTHING COMPARED
TO A SUMMER

623
00:33:59,078 --> 00:34:00,831
IN THE EVERGLADES.

624
00:34:00,873 --> 00:34:04,125
AT LEAST THERE AREN'T
ANY MOSQUITOES.

625
00:34:06,837 --> 00:34:08,254
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

626
00:34:08,296 --> 00:34:09,506
OVER THERE.

627
00:34:09,548 --> 00:34:12,217
LOOKS LIKE A GOOD PLACE
TO SET UP CAMP.

628
00:34:12,258 --> 00:34:15,012
YOUR VESSEL WILL NEVER
FIND US HERE.

629
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:18,598
DON'T UNDERESTIMATE
CAPTAIN ARCHER.

630
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,863
YOU'RE BLEEDING.

631
00:34:32,905 --> 00:34:34,280
IT'S JUST A SCRATCH.

632
00:34:34,322 --> 00:34:36,241
REMOVE YOUR UNIFORM.

633
00:34:36,282 --> 00:34:37,450
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT LATER.

634
00:34:37,492 --> 00:34:38,618
WE HAVE NO IDEA

635
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:40,579
WHAT MICROBES LIVE
IN THIS ENVIRONMENT.

636
00:34:40,620 --> 00:34:41,955
IT COULD BECOME INFECTED.

637
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:43,498
I SAID LATER!

638
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:46,752
YOU'RE MY ONLY HOPE
OF SURVIVING HERE, MR. TUCKER.

639
00:34:46,793 --> 00:34:48,962
I DON'T INTEND TO LET YOU DIE.

640
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:50,589
[ SIGHS ]

641
00:35:20,201 --> 00:35:22,120
THIS ONE.

642
00:35:29,127 --> 00:35:31,630
HOLD STILL.

643
00:35:31,671 --> 00:35:34,257
THE PROVISIONS WON'T LAST
FOR MORE THAN A DAY.

644
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:37,928
IT SOUNDS LIKE THERE'S
PLENTY OF WILDLIFE.

645
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:41,222
I GREW UP IN A PLACE
KIND OF LIKE THIS.

646
00:35:41,264 --> 00:35:44,225
I DON'T THINK
WE'RE GOING TO STARVE.

647
00:35:44,267 --> 00:35:47,312
AND I CAN USE THE THRUSTER
ASSEMBLY FROM THE POD

648
00:35:47,353 --> 00:35:51,149
TO START A FIRE,
BOIL SOME WATER.

649
00:35:53,068 --> 00:35:54,861
THANKS.

650
00:35:54,903 --> 00:35:57,114
YOU'RE WELCOME.

651
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:12,129
THAT'S THE BEST YOU COULD DO?

652
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,673
THERE'S VERY LITTLE DRY WOOD.

653
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:16,466
KEEP LOOKING.

654
00:36:21,054 --> 00:36:22,347
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

655
00:36:22,388 --> 00:36:24,641
I'M NOT YOUR SERVANT.

656
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:26,059
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO WAS RAISED

657
00:36:26,101 --> 00:36:27,602
IN A PRIMITIVE ENVIRONMENT.

658
00:36:27,644 --> 00:36:29,729
<i>YOU</i> FIND THE WOOD.

659
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:31,815
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

660
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:34,275
YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY BETTER SUITED
TO PHYSICAL LABOR.

661
00:36:34,317 --> 00:36:37,403
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
WE'RE NOT IN A PALACE.

662
00:36:37,445 --> 00:36:38,780
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF.

663
00:36:38,822 --> 00:36:40,239
YOU WON'T SURVIVE
WITHOUT MY HELP,

664
00:36:40,281 --> 00:36:42,408
SO IT SEEMS TO ME
THAT I'M THE ONE IN CHARGE.

665
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:43,827
THE KING OF THE SWAMP!

666
00:36:43,869 --> 00:36:45,704
NOW GET YOUR ASS OUT THERE
AND DON'T COME BACK

667
00:36:45,745 --> 00:36:47,372
WITHOUT AN ARMFUL OF DRY WOOD!

668
00:36:47,413 --> 00:36:50,083
I SHOULD HAVE YOU IMPRISONED
FOR SPEAKING TO ME THAT WAY.

669
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:51,584
YOU SHOULD GIVE ME A MEDAL.

670
00:36:51,626 --> 00:36:53,336
YOU'D BE DEAD
IF IT WEREN'T FOR ME!

671
00:36:53,378 --> 00:36:55,922
I'M BEGINNING TO THINK
THAT WOULD BE PREFERABLE.

672
00:36:55,964 --> 00:36:59,467
I DOUBT THE COMMONERS
BACK HOME WOULD COMPLAIN.

673
00:37:03,429 --> 00:37:05,515
HOW DARE YOU!

674
00:37:05,557 --> 00:37:08,143
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO TOOK A SWING AT ME!

675
00:37:08,185 --> 00:37:10,020
YOU INSULTED
THE FIRST MONARCH!

676
00:37:10,062 --> 00:37:11,771
I'M JUST A PETTY
COMMONER, REMEMBER?

677
00:37:11,813 --> 00:37:13,690
RAISED ON A PRIMI--

678
00:37:45,513 --> 00:37:48,100
[ BEEPING SOUND ]

679
00:37:56,566 --> 00:38:00,070
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

680
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:16,044
WHAT'S WRONG?

681
00:38:16,086 --> 00:38:17,462
A HOMING BEACON.

682
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:19,798
UNLESS I'M WAY OFF,

683
00:38:19,839 --> 00:38:21,424
SOMEONE JUST LOCKED ON TO IT.

684
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:22,508
YOUR VESSEL?

685
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:24,469
NO WAY TO TELL.

686
00:39:20,608 --> 00:39:23,528
[ LAUGHS ]

687
00:39:23,569 --> 00:39:26,072
[ GRUNTING ]

688
00:39:30,618 --> 00:39:34,539
[ GROWLING ]

689
00:39:45,008 --> 00:39:46,676
LEAVE HIM.

690
00:40:02,608 --> 00:40:05,403
LET'S FIND HIS WEAPON.

691
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:12,369
THERE'S SOMEONE ELSE HERE.

692
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:32,389
ARCHER: TRIP?

693
00:40:36,059 --> 00:40:38,019
THIS A BAD TIME?

694
00:40:44,567 --> 00:40:49,155
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SEPTEMBER 12, 2152.

695
00:40:49,197 --> 00:40:51,824
WE'VE RENDEZVOUSED
WITH A KRIOS BATTLE CRUISER,

696
00:40:51,866 --> 00:40:55,494
WHICH HAS TAKEN THE KIDNAPPERS
INTO CUSTODY.

697
00:40:55,536 --> 00:40:58,497
SO, WHEN DO YOU ASCEND?

698
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:00,625
246 DAYS.

699
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:02,543
IT'S A LONG SHOT,

700
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:04,712
BUT MAYBE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
<i>WILL GET THE CHANCE</i>

701
00:41:04,754 --> 00:41:07,132
TO VISIT KRIOS PRIME
BEFORE THEN.

702
00:41:07,173 --> 00:41:09,175
OF COURSE, FROM WHAT
YOU'VE TOLD ME,

703
00:41:09,217 --> 00:41:11,844
I DOUBT YOUR FAMILY
WOULD LET ME SEE YOU.

704
00:41:11,886 --> 00:41:13,888
I DOUBT THEY WOULD.

705
00:41:13,930 --> 00:41:16,599
BUT ONCE I'VE BEEN MADE
FIRST MONARCH,

706
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:20,645
I'LL HAVE THE AUTHORITY
TO CHANGE THE RULES.

707
00:41:20,686 --> 00:41:24,357
WHAT KIND OF CHANGES?

708
00:41:24,399 --> 00:41:26,734
COME VISIT ME.

709
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:29,446
PERHAPS YOU'LL FIND OUT.
